@database DWEBP
@master "DWEBP.1"
@remark "manual page source format generated by PolyglotMan v3.2 available at http://polyglotman.sourceforge.net/"
@wordwrap
@tab 8

@node sect0 "Name"
dwebp - decompress a WebP file to an image file 
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
@{b}dwebp@{ub} [@{i}options@{ui}]@{i} input_file.webp@{ui} 

@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
This manual page documents the @{b}dwebp@{ub} command. @{b}dwebp@{ub} decompresses WebP files into PNG, PAM, PPM or PGM images. 


@endnode

@node sect3 "Options"
The basic options are: 

· @{b}-h@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Print usage summary. @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-version@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Print the version number (as major.minor.revision) and exit. @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-o string@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Specify the name of the output file (as PNG format by default). @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-pam@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Change the output format to PAM (retains alpha). @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-ppm@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Change the output format to PPM (discards alpha). @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-pgm@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Change the output format to PGM. The output consist of luma/chroma samples instead of RGB, using the ICM4 layout. This option is mainly for verification and debugging purpose. @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-nofancy@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Don't use the fancy upscaler for YUV420. This may lead to jaggy edges (especially the red ones), but should be faster. @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-nofilter@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Don't use the in-loop filtering process even if it is required by the bitstream. This may produce visible blocks on the non-compliant output, but will make the decoding faster. @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-mt@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Use multi-threading for decoding, if possible. @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-crop x_position y_position width height@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Crop the decoded picture to a rectangle with top-left corner at coordinates (@{b}x_position@{ub}, @{b}y_position@{ub}) and size @{b}width@{ub} x @{b}height@{ub}. This cropping area must be fully contained within the source rectangle. The top-left corner will be snapped to even coordinates if needed. This option is meant to reduce the memory needed for cropping large images. Note: the cropping is applied @{i}before@{ui} any scaling. @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-scale width height@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Rescale the decoded picture to dimension @{b}width@{ub} x @{b}height@{ub}. This option is mostly intended to reducing the memory needed to decode large images, when only a small version is needed (thumbnail, preview, etc.).  Note: scaling is applied @{i}after@{ui} cropping. @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-v@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Print extra information (decoding time in particular). @{lindent 0}

· @{b}-noasm@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Disable all assembly optimizations.  @{lindent 0}


@endnode

@node sect4 "Bugs"
Please report all bugs to our issue tracker: http://code.google.com/p/webp/issues 
Patches welcome! See this page to get started: http://www.webmproject.org/code/contribute/submitting-patches/  
@endnode

@node sect5 "Examples"
dwebp picture.webp -o output.png 
dwebp picture.webp -ppm -o output.ppm  
@endnode

@node sect6 "Authors"
@{b}dwebp@{ub} was written by the WebP team. 
The latest source tree is available at http://www.webmproject.org/code This manual page was written by Pascal Massimino <pascal.massimino@gmail.com>, for the Debian project (and may be used by others).  


@endnode

@node sect7 "See Also"
@{"@{b}cwebp@{ub}(1)" link %s.%scwebp1/main}. 
Please refer to http://developers.google.com/speed/webp/ for additional information. 

@{b}Output file format details@{ub}

PAM: http://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pam.html 
PGM: http://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pgm.html 
PPM: http://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/ppm.html 
PNG: http://www.libpng.org/pub/png/png-sitemap.html#info 
@endnode
